WEBVTT

00:00.042 --> 00:02.084
<i>Previously on "Once Upon a Time"...</i>

00:02.085 --> 00:05.272
Whoever killed our doctor
tried to kill our baker, too.

00:05.292 --> 00:07.191
Someone's killing witches.

00:07.209 --> 00:09.260
HOOK: So, you're just gonna
abandon this baby here?

00:09.292 --> 00:11.084
The only way I can escape this prison

00:11.134 --> 00:13.885
is by leaving someone in my
bloodline to take my place.

00:13.948 --> 00:16.749
Look familiar? It's part of
the Curse of the Poisoned Heart.

00:16.784 --> 00:18.450
It appears when you're touched

00:18.486 --> 00:19.852
by the one you can't be with.

00:19.887 --> 00:22.621
Tonight is the night you're
finally gonna give my mom

00:22.657 --> 00:24.023
true love's kiss.

00:24.058 --> 00:26.692
LUCY: "If true love's kiss
should ever break the curse,

00:26.727 --> 00:28.527
Henry Mills would surely die."

00:28.994 --> 00:30.594
[GASPS] Mom!

00:30.619 --> 00:32.386
[PANTING]

00:36.834 --> 00:39.585
That painting is gorgeous, Alice.

00:39.640 --> 00:41.774
The calm before the storm.

00:41.809 --> 00:43.375
I don't think I like it.

00:43.411 --> 00:44.610
How is that possible?

00:44.645 --> 00:46.912
It might be your best one yet.

00:46.948 --> 00:49.214
It's... I mean, it's beautiful.

00:49.250 --> 00:50.916
It's just...

00:50.952 --> 00:53.016
it makes me want to see the real ocean.

00:54.296 --> 00:56.029
I'm done painting for a while.

00:58.000 --> 01:04.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:05.209 --> 01:07.251
I'm sorry you're trapped
in here, Starfish.

01:07.252 --> 01:09.459
I know it's not fair.

01:10.315 --> 01:12.091
But you know what?

01:12.116 --> 01:14.750
I might have something
that'll make you smile.

01:16.697 --> 01:19.069
I was saving it for your birthday,

01:19.104 --> 01:22.973
but today is better.

01:26.111 --> 01:27.644
Is it sand?

01:27.679 --> 01:29.646
Well, I figured if I
couldn't take you to the sea,

01:29.667 --> 01:31.709
then I'd bring a piece
of the sea to you.

01:31.806 --> 01:33.583
Thank you, Papa.

01:33.799 --> 01:35.251
I love you.

01:35.384 --> 01:37.154
I love you, too.

01:37.189 --> 01:38.188
[GASPS]

01:38.209 --> 01:40.960
- [CHOKING]
- Papa! What's wrong?

01:40.993 --> 01:43.360
Papa! What's happening to you?!

01:43.395 --> 01:44.528
Papa!

01:44.563 --> 01:45.595
GOTHEL: I am.

01:49.401 --> 01:52.669
No!

01:53.906 --> 01:54.871
[SCREAMS]

01:54.907 --> 01:56.339
[PANTING]

02:03.626 --> 02:05.210
Hey.

02:07.000 --> 02:08.667
Don't worry.

02:08.720 --> 02:09.953
It was just a bad dream.

02:09.988 --> 02:11.421
I saw the witch again.

02:11.456 --> 02:12.856
She's coming for me.

02:12.891 --> 02:14.691
It was just a nightmare.

02:14.726 --> 02:16.927
It's not! It's real!
You have to believe me.

02:19.177 --> 02:22.799
You do see the world
in a special way, Alice.

02:22.834 --> 02:26.036
If you say the dream means
something, then I believe you.

02:31.343 --> 02:32.904
What are you doing?

02:34.029 --> 02:35.612
Making sure the dream doesn't come true.

02:35.647 --> 02:37.380
I'm getting you out of this
tower, once and for all.

02:37.416 --> 02:39.015
But how? You've tried everything.

02:39.051 --> 02:40.550
Almost everything.

02:40.586 --> 02:41.952
The truth is...

02:41.987 --> 02:43.553
there is one more thing I can try.

02:43.589 --> 02:45.514
It's a dark path that
I always feared to take,

02:45.539 --> 02:49.292
but I don't have any other choice.

02:54.019 --> 02:55.799
Keep this close by.

02:55.834 --> 02:57.767
To remember me.

02:57.803 --> 02:59.336
I'm scared, Papa.

02:59.371 --> 03:00.870
What if something happens to you?

03:00.906 --> 03:04.107
What, happens to me? Come on.

03:04.142 --> 03:05.141
I'll be fine.

03:05.177 --> 03:07.344
And I swear...

03:08.148 --> 03:10.470
I will return as soon as I can.

03:14.375 --> 03:16.792
Then take this to remember me.

03:21.093 --> 03:23.693
My little rook.

03:23.709 --> 03:27.418
You are the bravest girl I know.

03:27.466 --> 03:29.499
Look, soon all of this will be over,

03:29.534 --> 03:33.970
and all the chess pieces
will be together again.

04:03.918 --> 04:05.127
Morning, Detective!

04:05.137 --> 04:06.169
I'm glad you're here.

04:06.204 --> 04:07.704
I could really use a
good match right now.

04:07.739 --> 04:09.639
Look, I'm working. I don't
have time to play games.

04:09.675 --> 04:11.341
We can all make time for games.

04:11.376 --> 04:13.376
They can help us out on our bad days.

04:13.412 --> 04:15.645
And I have a feeling it's
gonna be one of those.

04:15.681 --> 04:17.213
What are you talking about?

04:17.249 --> 04:19.949
Well, just a feeling...

04:20.000 --> 04:22.167
something awful's gonna happen.

04:22.187 --> 04:24.854
My head feels a bit off,

04:24.890 --> 04:26.389
but it's nothing a good
game won't clear up!

04:26.425 --> 04:27.490
I'm sure that it would,

04:27.526 --> 04:30.994
but I have to focus
on my case right now.

04:32.364 --> 04:35.131
People are in danger. It's important.

04:36.876 --> 04:38.959
- And I'm not?
- I'm not saying that. I'm not.

04:38.960 --> 04:40.501
I'm just... [SIGHS]

04:40.542 --> 04:43.084
right now, I really need you to go home.

04:43.108 --> 04:44.441
Yeah?

04:44.476 --> 04:45.442
Right.

04:45.477 --> 04:47.477
Yeah, of course.

04:51.482 --> 04:53.524
Hey, Tilly.

04:55.620 --> 04:57.487
What's the matter with her?

04:57.522 --> 04:58.955
I'm not sure.

04:58.990 --> 05:00.450
It's just...

05:01.559 --> 05:03.526
Tilly being Tilly.

05:04.730 --> 05:06.536
So, what's the word on our Blind Baker?

05:06.561 --> 05:09.332
Enjoying the finest medical
care in Hyperion Heights.

05:09.368 --> 05:11.701
I posted a patrol outside her room.

05:11.737 --> 05:14.204
My suspicion is, this
killer goes for easy prey,

05:14.250 --> 05:16.667
so I've just made things a
little bit more difficult.

05:16.708 --> 05:19.909
With a bit of luck,
it'll help flush them out.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.611
So, everyone in that cult is in danger,

05:21.626 --> 05:23.043
but we don't have a
bloody clue who they are.

05:23.115 --> 05:25.715
Well, we don't. But
Eloise Gardener does.

05:25.751 --> 05:29.285
She may have decided to vanish
in the wake of Victoria's death.

05:29.321 --> 05:30.954
But that doesn't mean
to say we won't find her.

05:30.989 --> 05:32.389
We will.

05:32.424 --> 05:35.024
She's the key that's
gonna open all the locks.

05:35.060 --> 05:37.827
Then, by all means, let's open them.

05:37.863 --> 05:40.363
I think it's time we
all had a little talk.

05:50.709 --> 05:52.418
Roni.

05:52.444 --> 05:54.691
Hey. How's it going?

05:54.709 --> 05:56.792
- What are you doing out here?
- [SIGHS]

05:56.815 --> 05:59.449
Finishing up a really long night shift.

05:59.484 --> 06:00.650
Given the company's called Swyft,

06:00.685 --> 06:04.053
you'd think it'd go fast, but... nope.

06:04.089 --> 06:05.822
What are you doing out here?

06:05.857 --> 06:08.691
'Cause you are definitely
not a morning person.

06:08.727 --> 06:11.494
I, uh, actually had a meeting...

06:11.530 --> 06:14.197
with one of my suppliers.

06:14.232 --> 06:16.232
At 6:00 a.m.?

06:16.268 --> 06:18.034
In that?

06:18.069 --> 06:19.202
[SIGHS]

06:19.237 --> 06:21.838
Okay, fine. There wasn't a meeting.

06:21.873 --> 06:24.040
Now stop giving me that look.

06:24.075 --> 06:25.141
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

06:25.177 --> 06:28.678
I was catching up with an old boyfriend,

06:28.713 --> 06:29.979
okay?

06:30.015 --> 06:32.782
At least one of us had a good night.

06:32.818 --> 06:34.717
Oh.

06:34.753 --> 06:38.188
Henry, if something's
wrong, you can tell me.

06:38.223 --> 06:39.689
I went to Jacinda's last night.

06:39.724 --> 06:41.524
Oh.

06:41.560 --> 06:43.526
I'm sorry. I just didn't realize

06:43.562 --> 06:45.628
that you two were back on.

06:45.664 --> 06:47.197
Well, not anymore.

06:47.232 --> 06:48.965
'Cause all of a sudden,
Lucy broke it up.

06:49.000 --> 06:50.600
And then... And then
she got super weird.

06:50.635 --> 06:52.302
It was, like, suddenly,

06:52.337 --> 06:56.973
I wasn't good enough
for her mom or something.

06:57.008 --> 06:59.709
Hmm.

06:59.744 --> 07:01.811
Well...

07:01.847 --> 07:03.880
kids can be complicated, huh?

07:03.915 --> 07:05.715
Yeah.

07:05.750 --> 07:07.750
Hey, why don't you come inside?

07:07.786 --> 07:12.722
And I'll fix you some eggs
and a shoulder to cry on.

07:12.757 --> 07:14.791
Thanks. I could probably use both.

07:16.584 --> 07:19.335
You have a chance to save
some lives here, all right?

07:19.364 --> 07:20.363
All we need is a list

07:20.398 --> 07:21.664
of the members of the cult,

07:21.700 --> 07:24.133
and then we can get to
them before the killer does.

07:24.169 --> 07:25.480
ELOISE: We're not a cult.

07:25.505 --> 07:28.505
We're a group of women
with shared ideals.

07:28.540 --> 07:29.939
Why do people like you

07:29.975 --> 07:31.140
always have to put a label on that?

07:31.209 --> 07:34.777
Like cult or coven or... I don't know...

07:34.813 --> 07:36.246
witches?

07:36.281 --> 07:39.015
Is that label so far astray?

07:39.050 --> 07:41.571
Where were you the night
of Victoria Belfrey's death?

07:42.721 --> 07:45.421
I'm sorry. Am I a suspect now?

07:45.457 --> 07:49.158
And since when was this
about me, Detective Weaver?

07:49.194 --> 07:50.226
I came here

07:50.262 --> 07:51.461
to help you find a killer.

07:51.777 --> 07:53.067
Of course you did.

07:53.092 --> 07:56.799
I apologize for my partner.

07:56.835 --> 07:59.335
I don't want an apology.

07:59.371 --> 08:00.837
I want him gone.

08:00.872 --> 08:02.939
Hm. You and I always have

08:02.974 --> 08:06.142
such nice conversations,
Detective Rogers.

08:06.177 --> 08:10.013
So, if I can't talk to you
alone, I don't talk at all.

08:16.000 --> 08:18.876
You do not want to go in there yourself.

08:18.898 --> 08:22.366
That woman's life's
work is manipulation.

08:22.401 --> 08:24.601
Yeah, she manipulates
lonely, lost girls.

08:24.637 --> 08:26.303
And I'm none of those things.

08:26.338 --> 08:28.739
I'll be fine. It's not
like she's actually a witch.

08:28.774 --> 08:31.141
Yeah, well, whatever
she is, I assure you,

08:31.176 --> 08:33.477
she's not going to give
up her answers easily.

08:33.501 --> 08:35.376
Why? 'Cause she won't talk to you?

08:36.982 --> 08:39.982
I spent years looking for her.

08:40.019 --> 08:42.085
Yeah, she turned out
different than I expected,

08:42.125 --> 08:44.334
but I know her.

08:44.356 --> 08:45.489
She likes to be in control.

08:45.524 --> 08:47.238
Yeah, you got that part right.

08:47.263 --> 08:49.803
Yeah, so I'll let her
think she's in control.

08:49.828 --> 08:52.129
Then I'll rope her in,
break open the case.

08:52.164 --> 08:53.297
Hey, hey, hey.

08:53.332 --> 08:54.932
I'm trying to help you here.

08:54.967 --> 08:57.434
I want to solve this case
just as badly as you do.

08:57.469 --> 08:59.336
So, go in there, get your answers,

08:59.375 --> 09:00.750
but whatever happens...

09:00.773 --> 09:03.550
do not let that woman inside your head.

09:05.542 --> 09:08.209
[RUMPLESTILTSKIN GIGGLING]

09:09.214 --> 09:11.315
Come out where I can see you.

09:11.350 --> 09:12.516
RUMPLESTILTSKIN: [GIGGLING]

09:12.551 --> 09:14.785
Ooh, it's Captain Hook!

09:14.820 --> 09:16.320
Oh, what a lovely treat!

09:16.355 --> 09:19.790
Oh, come closer. Clos-s-er.

09:23.128 --> 09:24.561
[GIGGLES]

09:24.597 --> 09:27.331
You know, it's been so long
since I talked to anyone

09:27.366 --> 09:29.533
except rats and leeches.

09:29.568 --> 09:31.401
Oh, I didn't come for the conversation.

09:31.437 --> 09:33.403
Of course you didn't, dearie!

09:33.439 --> 09:38.575
And so, what brings Captain Hook home?

09:38.611 --> 09:42.512
Finally ready to seize his revenge?

09:42.548 --> 09:45.849
Finally ready to kill me?

09:45.884 --> 09:47.484
Or try?

09:47.519 --> 09:49.519
I'm not that man anymore.

09:49.555 --> 09:53.123
I finally learned what it meant to live.

09:54.893 --> 09:57.594
I'm willing to set aside
my revenge to ask...

09:57.630 --> 09:58.862
Hmm?

09:58.897 --> 10:00.163
To ask you for your help.

10:00.199 --> 10:01.765
[CACKLES]

10:01.800 --> 10:04.001
[SNIFFING]

10:04.036 --> 10:05.102
Yes!

10:05.137 --> 10:06.837
I thought I smelled desperation.

10:06.872 --> 10:08.171
My speciality.

10:08.207 --> 10:10.507
So, tell me, what's the problem, eh?

10:10.542 --> 10:12.175
Is it a plague? A woman? A curse?

10:12.211 --> 10:13.276
A daughter.

10:13.312 --> 10:14.711
A witch has locked her in a tower,

10:14.747 --> 10:18.715
and I-I need magic to set her free.

10:18.751 --> 10:21.318
Oh, well, that's doubly tragic.

10:21.353 --> 10:24.121
For you have come to the wrong place.

10:24.156 --> 10:25.822
No magic here.

10:25.858 --> 10:28.125
I know this place drains your power.

10:28.160 --> 10:29.660
Yes.

10:29.695 --> 10:30.861
Drains me.

10:30.896 --> 10:33.030
But if you help me...

10:33.065 --> 10:37.200
If you help me free my
daughter from her prison...

10:37.236 --> 10:39.636
I'll finally free you from yours.

10:42.508 --> 10:44.608
Uh, a d-deal?

10:44.626 --> 10:46.502
- Yes, a deal.
- Indeed! Oh!

10:46.545 --> 10:48.512
[GIGGLES] Oh, I remember!

10:48.547 --> 10:50.547
I used to love those!

10:50.582 --> 10:52.749
There is something.

10:52.785 --> 10:57.621
A magic weapon with the
power to shatter any prison.

10:57.656 --> 11:00.090
But it's terribly difficult to obtain.

11:00.125 --> 11:01.525
Terribly, terribly, terribly difficult.

11:01.560 --> 11:02.926
Just tell me where it is.

11:02.961 --> 11:04.928
It's not a question
of <i> where,</i> dearie...

11:04.963 --> 11:06.396
but <i> who.</i>

11:06.432 --> 11:10.467
This magic is in the hands
of another famous captain.

11:10.502 --> 11:12.736
And you and I both know...

11:12.771 --> 11:17.441
pirates don't give up what's
theirs without a fight.

11:17.788 --> 11:19.554
[GIGGLES]

11:21.834 --> 11:23.752
All right. You win.

11:23.782 --> 11:25.582
Detective Weaver's
gone out for a coffee.

11:25.617 --> 11:27.884
It's just us now.

11:27.918 --> 11:31.335
Oh, I doubt he went anywhere.

11:32.858 --> 11:35.258
<i>But as long as I can look
at your face and not his,</i>

11:35.294 --> 11:36.793
I'm a happy girl.

11:36.829 --> 11:39.329
Glad to hear that.

11:39.364 --> 11:40.997
Have you ever thought
about taking a razor

11:41.033 --> 11:43.427
to that face of yours, Detective?

11:44.169 --> 11:46.203
I bet you look nice clean-shaven.

11:46.238 --> 11:48.205
Tell me,

11:48.240 --> 11:52.442
why did you come in today?

11:52.478 --> 11:54.711
Because I want the
same thing that you do.

11:54.747 --> 11:58.281
I want to prevent women
like me from being killed.

11:58.317 --> 12:00.117
Well, tell me who they
are, and I'll protect them.

12:00.152 --> 12:02.486
And you really think
you're capable of that?

12:02.521 --> 12:04.588
It's not that easy.

12:04.623 --> 12:06.156
First you have to know
who you really are.

12:06.191 --> 12:08.391
And right now, you have no idea.

12:08.427 --> 12:10.026
And you think you do?

12:10.062 --> 12:14.197
I think the answer's closer
than you ever imagined.

12:16.250 --> 12:19.834
A picture really is worth
a thousand words, isn't it?

12:21.412 --> 12:23.707
I wonder what this one means, deep down.

12:23.742 --> 12:26.537
It's just a doodle. It's an old habit.

12:26.732 --> 12:29.212
Maybe older than you know.

12:29.248 --> 12:33.522
There are so many patterns
around you you can't see yet.

12:33.547 --> 12:35.519
Patterns that govern your actions.

12:35.554 --> 12:36.486
And mine.

12:36.522 --> 12:37.821
And the killer's.

12:37.856 --> 12:39.456
What kind of patterns?

12:39.491 --> 12:41.024
If you want to learn the
truth about the killer,

12:41.059 --> 12:44.694
first, you need to learn
the truth about yourself.

12:44.730 --> 12:46.163
All right, well, you
seem to know everything.

12:46.198 --> 12:47.831
Why don't you just tell me?

12:47.866 --> 12:50.567
Oh, I can't see all
the patterns. I can't.

12:50.602 --> 12:52.769
But I do know how to search for them.

12:52.805 --> 12:54.704
And if you're ready to uncover yours,

12:54.740 --> 12:58.341
you just need to do
one small thing for me.

13:09.584 --> 13:11.085
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

13:13.625 --> 13:15.826
Hey, Luce.

13:15.861 --> 13:16.793
You hungry?

13:16.829 --> 13:18.161
No, not really.

13:18.197 --> 13:19.963
I made mac and cheese.

13:19.998 --> 13:23.266
It's your favorite, with
those little farm animals.

13:23.302 --> 13:25.368
They're so cute!

13:25.404 --> 13:27.571
Mom, I'm not 6 anymore.

13:27.626 --> 13:29.626
- I'll just put it here.
- [SIGHS]

13:29.641 --> 13:32.442
Whatever you want. I
gotta finish my homework.

13:36.315 --> 13:38.748
Hey.

13:38.784 --> 13:40.984
We haven't had a chance
to talk about last night.

13:41.019 --> 13:42.953
What about last night?

13:42.988 --> 13:44.921
<i>You</i> tell <i> me.</i>

13:44.957 --> 13:47.991
First you wanted me
and Henry to be alone.

13:48.026 --> 13:50.293
And then, all of a sudden, you didn't.

13:50.329 --> 13:51.485
It's just...

13:51.510 --> 13:54.970
I've been really overwhelmed
after the hospital.

13:55.384 --> 13:57.834
And Grandma dying.

13:57.870 --> 14:00.470
I need you around, Mom.

14:00.505 --> 14:03.173
And I don't want you
spending time with...

14:03.208 --> 14:04.774
some guy.

14:06.511 --> 14:08.211
"Some guy"?

14:08.247 --> 14:10.313
You loved him.

14:10.349 --> 14:13.450
And isn't he still your favorite writer?

14:13.485 --> 14:15.752
[SIGHS] He used to be,

14:15.787 --> 14:18.955
because I thought his
fairy tales were real.

14:19.269 --> 14:22.292
But then bad things
happen, and you grow up.

14:22.327 --> 14:26.463
So, maybe I don't believe
in fairy tales anymore.

14:31.501 --> 14:34.168
And I don't want you to see him again.

14:38.209 --> 14:39.726
Where the hell are you going?

14:39.751 --> 14:41.606
To give Eloise what she wants.

14:41.626 --> 14:42.709
Well, how is that gonna help?

14:42.732 --> 14:44.732
She asked for your favorite painting?

14:44.767 --> 14:46.967
The woman's out of her
mind. Worse... dangerous.

14:47.000 --> 14:48.000
And very perceptive.

14:48.037 --> 14:49.975
How does she even know that I can paint?

14:50.000 --> 14:51.125
Excellent question.

14:51.196 --> 14:53.363
Perhaps her insight
should give you pause.

14:53.398 --> 14:54.631
Well, it doesn't.

14:54.666 --> 14:57.767
Right, if she knows something,
I'm willing to play along.

14:57.803 --> 14:59.536
I thought you wanted to find the killer.

14:59.584 --> 15:00.876
If she has the answers,

15:00.876 --> 15:03.043
- then a painting is a small price to pay.
- [SCOFFS]

15:03.108 --> 15:05.842
If you think that, you
don't understand the price.

15:06.667 --> 15:08.168
Well, whatever the price is,

15:08.193 --> 15:10.250
believe me, I'm willing to pay it.

15:10.315 --> 15:11.748
[VEHICLE DOOR CLOSES]

15:11.792 --> 15:13.251
[ENGINE STARTS]

15:18.542 --> 15:20.625
[MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS]

15:20.667 --> 15:22.209
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- Captain.

15:22.227 --> 15:23.293
Is it really you?

15:23.328 --> 15:24.794
Mr. Smee.

15:24.830 --> 15:26.096
It's been too long.

15:26.131 --> 15:27.264
Hey, how's the <i> Jolly Roger?</i>

15:27.299 --> 15:28.465
Shipshape and ready to set sail.

15:28.500 --> 15:30.166
If you want her back, just say the word.

15:30.202 --> 15:33.570
Well, as much as I miss her,
I'm here for another treasure.

15:33.605 --> 15:36.907
I've been told that the
captain who holds it is here.

15:36.942 --> 15:38.575
A man named Ahab.

15:38.610 --> 15:41.544
AHAB: If it's Captain Ahab you seek...

15:41.584 --> 15:43.502
then your search is over.

15:44.041 --> 15:49.052
Though your trouble,
alas, has just begun.

15:49.087 --> 15:51.521
It's dangerous to seek me out, old man.

15:51.546 --> 15:56.559
Well, it's a dangerous
thing to call me "old man."

15:56.595 --> 15:58.028
Ah.

15:58.083 --> 16:00.998
- The legendary Captain Hook.
- Mm-hmm.

16:00.999 --> 16:03.099
Well, it's nice to finally meet you.

16:03.135 --> 16:05.101
And, you know, people,

16:05.144 --> 16:07.911
they... they always tell
me that... that... that I...

16:07.940 --> 16:10.840
am what you used to be, huh?

16:10.876 --> 16:13.009
No, <i>I'm</i> what I used to be, mate.

16:13.045 --> 16:14.644
[LAUGHS]

16:14.680 --> 16:16.513
Care to prove it, hmm?

16:16.548 --> 16:19.115
Well, look, I'm not
interested in fighting.

16:19.151 --> 16:22.352
I'm here looking for a magical weapon.

16:22.387 --> 16:23.553
Maui's Fishhook.

16:23.588 --> 16:26.690
Now, I've been told that
you've taken possession of it.

16:27.019 --> 16:28.318
[CHUCKLES]

16:28.334 --> 16:30.085
I have.

16:30.667 --> 16:35.251
But no washed-up former pirate

16:35.267 --> 16:37.901
is gonna take it from me.

16:38.163 --> 16:40.063
Careful with those threats, lad.

16:40.088 --> 16:44.194
If you really know who I am,
then you know how this will end.

16:46.958 --> 16:48.858
Anyway, I'm not interested in bloodshed.

16:51.149 --> 16:52.782
I see you have a taste for the dice.

16:52.818 --> 16:55.785
Now, how about we place a wager, right?

16:55.821 --> 17:00.256
Your magical fish barb
for, let's say, the, um...

17:00.292 --> 17:01.992
the <i> Jolly Roger</i> herself?

17:02.027 --> 17:03.893
[CHUCKLES]

17:03.929 --> 17:05.561
SMEE: Three dice.

17:05.597 --> 17:07.630
One roll.

17:07.665 --> 17:10.402
And may the best captain win.

17:18.626 --> 17:20.876
Oh. That's quite a toss.

17:20.910 --> 17:22.112
It's gonna be hard to beat that.

17:22.146 --> 17:25.337
But Lady Luck has
been on my side before.

17:34.876 --> 17:38.043
[LAUGHTER]

17:38.406 --> 17:40.339
Well, come on, then.

17:43.280 --> 17:45.402
Sorry, mate.

17:45.437 --> 17:48.271
I hope you have better luck
with that white fish of yours.

17:49.474 --> 17:54.277
You may be lucky, but
you're no pirate anymore.

17:54.312 --> 17:56.339
I see right through you.

17:56.364 --> 17:57.914
I'm sorry?

17:57.949 --> 18:02.085
You see, that white
whale keeps me sharp.

18:02.120 --> 18:03.253
But you...

18:03.288 --> 18:06.956
I heard that you gave up your crocodile.

18:06.992 --> 18:08.591
Don't believe everything you hear.

18:08.627 --> 18:10.693
People are talking...

18:10.729 --> 18:14.531
saying that Hook went soft.

18:15.031 --> 18:17.467
Lost your edge.

18:18.421 --> 18:20.373
You want to know what this is for?

18:20.398 --> 18:22.248
I'm gonna use it to kill the Dark One.

18:22.273 --> 18:25.608
Believe me, I never lose
sight of what matters most.

18:41.042 --> 18:42.084
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

18:43.709 --> 18:45.668
- Hey.
- IVY: Hey.

18:45.885 --> 18:48.298
I came as soon as I got your message.

18:48.323 --> 18:50.173
Uh, how you doing?

18:50.198 --> 18:51.768
Well, my mother's been dead for a week,

18:51.803 --> 18:55.105
I'm completely alone,
so I'm doing great.

18:55.140 --> 18:56.339
Oh, well, hey, if you...

18:56.374 --> 18:57.607
If you don't want me here, I can go.

18:57.642 --> 18:59.008
No, no. Stay.

18:59.513 --> 19:00.812
Sorry.

19:01.977 --> 19:03.451
Turns out the only thing

19:03.459 --> 19:05.584
harder than cleaning up
your dead mother's things

19:05.629 --> 19:08.296
is doing it by yourself.

19:08.348 --> 19:10.381
So, all this is hers, huh?

19:10.416 --> 19:11.549
Yep.

19:11.584 --> 19:13.184
Whoa.

19:13.459 --> 19:15.459
How many gold pens does one person need?

19:15.482 --> 19:16.520
[LAUGHS]

19:16.556 --> 19:19.402
She certainly didn't do
anything by half measures.

19:19.427 --> 19:23.794
But now I don't know what
to keep or what to sell or...

19:24.238 --> 19:26.030
what to do with my life.

19:26.065 --> 19:29.500
Ah. So we're talking about
more than office supplies here.

19:29.535 --> 19:32.003
Mother was the whole reason
I'm even in this town.

19:32.038 --> 19:33.604
I spent my whole life hating her,

19:33.640 --> 19:36.574
and then, at the end, it turns
out she loved me all along.

19:37.189 --> 19:38.542
Wasn't that a good thing?

19:38.625 --> 19:41.697
I don't know. I just feel kind of lost.

19:42.150 --> 19:43.281
I feel like you're the only person

19:43.334 --> 19:45.751
I can talk to about this.

19:45.752 --> 19:48.011
You understand me.

19:49.331 --> 19:51.689
I'm trying to.

19:51.724 --> 19:55.559
We both lost people that we care about.

19:55.595 --> 19:57.995
We're both wounded birds.

19:58.031 --> 19:59.030
Right?

19:59.174 --> 20:01.574
I mean, maybe...

20:01.824 --> 20:03.701
maybe we can fix each other.

20:06.125 --> 20:07.751
Mm. Uh, hey.

20:07.774 --> 20:11.309
That... This... This is
not what you need right now.

20:11.344 --> 20:12.510
Believe me, it is.

20:12.545 --> 20:13.511
No, wait, wait.

20:13.546 --> 20:16.447
Just stop. Stop.

20:16.482 --> 20:18.149
Listen.

20:18.184 --> 20:20.551
Listen, I get it, okay?

20:20.586 --> 20:22.853
When my family died, I...

20:22.889 --> 20:25.323
I tried all sorts of stupid
things to make me feel better.

20:25.375 --> 20:27.167
- Oh. So now I'm stupid?
- [SIGHS]

20:27.193 --> 20:28.559
No.

20:32.083 --> 20:34.500
No, you're not stupid. You're grieving.

20:34.534 --> 20:37.068
You're... You're trying
to grab onto something.

20:37.325 --> 20:39.136
It's just...

20:39.172 --> 20:41.572
I'm the wrong thing.

20:41.607 --> 20:44.141
Well, then I'm screwed,
Because guess what.

20:44.501 --> 20:47.252
- You're all I've got.
- Oh, come on. That's not true.

20:47.313 --> 20:50.681
Look, when I lost my
family, I had nobody left.

20:50.717 --> 20:52.316
Okay, I was completely alone.

20:52.352 --> 20:53.351
But you're not.

20:53.386 --> 20:55.353
You still have a sister.

20:55.924 --> 20:57.421
And a niece.

20:57.457 --> 20:59.657
Who hates me.

20:59.692 --> 21:01.625
They both hate me.

21:01.835 --> 21:03.728
They don't hate you.

21:03.763 --> 21:06.789
If you're trying to
figure out who Ivy is now,

21:07.632 --> 21:10.201
make her best person she can be.

21:10.236 --> 21:12.636
You can't change things
with the family you lost,

21:12.672 --> 21:14.972
so maybe, uh...

21:15.350 --> 21:17.784
you should try it with
the family you still have.

21:19.709 --> 21:22.335
Something's bad, something's
broken, something's wrong.

21:22.382 --> 21:24.515
It's all gonna go wrong.

21:24.550 --> 21:26.083
I'm not mad, I'm not mad.

21:26.119 --> 21:28.285
Tilly, Tilly. You can't be back here.

21:28.321 --> 21:29.553
Oh, hey, there, Weaver.

21:29.589 --> 21:31.589
Um, I'm glad to see
your face. [CHUCKLES]

21:31.624 --> 21:33.691
I came by earlier, but Rogers,

21:33.726 --> 21:35.025
he didn't want to play the game with me.

21:35.061 --> 21:36.527
I tried to warn him. I did.

21:36.562 --> 21:38.028
But there's bad things in the air.

21:38.064 --> 21:39.497
Tilly, Tilly, calm down.

21:39.542 --> 21:41.084
- Everything's fine.
- No, everything's not fine.

21:41.100 --> 21:42.466
You brought a monster in here,

21:42.502 --> 21:43.934
and I can see her for
what she really is!

21:43.970 --> 21:46.270
You know what? You're right.

21:46.305 --> 21:47.972
She <i> is</i> a monster.

21:48.007 --> 21:49.573
I believe you.

21:49.857 --> 21:51.123
Oh, you do?

21:51.167 --> 21:53.209
- Well, I know you better than most.
- [SIGHS]

21:53.246 --> 21:54.678
You see things others don't.

21:54.714 --> 21:56.747
And that's what makes you special.

22:00.353 --> 22:03.053
Uh, what's... what's that?

22:03.089 --> 22:04.054
It's a painting of mine.

22:04.090 --> 22:05.256
I thought I told you to go home.

22:05.291 --> 22:06.824
No, no, no. You can't
show this to the monster.

22:06.859 --> 22:08.058
She'll use it, and then
she'll try and hurt you,

22:08.094 --> 22:09.221
and I don't want you to be hurt!

22:09.246 --> 22:12.041
Get out of my way, or I'll
have to have you escorted out.

22:14.596 --> 22:16.167
[SIGHS]

22:16.202 --> 22:17.802
You told me you believed me.

22:17.837 --> 22:19.069
WEAVER: I do.

22:19.105 --> 22:20.971
And I promise... Nothing
bad's gonna happen,

22:21.007 --> 22:22.306
but right now...

22:22.591 --> 22:24.558
you have to go home.

22:26.313 --> 22:28.012
You both want me to leave?

22:28.047 --> 22:30.281
I'm sorry, but this is more important.

22:45.667 --> 22:47.084
That's...

23:01.000 --> 23:02.667
Dark One.

23:02.834 --> 23:03.793
RUMPLESTILTSKIN: Hmm?

23:03.848 --> 23:05.448
[GIGGLES] Yeah.

23:05.483 --> 23:08.151
Oh! Hook.

23:08.174 --> 23:10.966
Yes! It's Captain Hook.

23:11.042 --> 23:13.876
I brought what you asked for.

23:14.232 --> 23:15.918
Ohh!

23:15.960 --> 23:17.393
Oh, yes!

23:17.429 --> 23:18.995
[LAUGHING] Yes!

23:19.030 --> 23:20.730
Oh, the magic!

23:20.765 --> 23:23.733
Closer. Bring the magic closer.

23:23.751 --> 23:25.751
Come on. Break the bars.

23:25.792 --> 23:27.751
Break the bars. Be a good boy.

23:27.806 --> 23:30.440
You and me! You and me. Look at us.

23:30.459 --> 23:33.001
The Captain and the
Crocodile working together.

23:33.044 --> 23:34.043
Who ever would have thunk it?

23:34.078 --> 23:36.112
Don't push your luck.

23:36.147 --> 23:38.080
Now let's break Alice out of that tower.

23:38.116 --> 23:39.449
Tell me how this thing works.

23:39.648 --> 23:41.045
AHAB: Oi.

23:42.053 --> 23:44.320
So the rumors are true, hmm?

23:44.355 --> 23:46.842
Captain Hook has gone soft.

23:46.873 --> 23:48.591
Ahab.

23:48.626 --> 23:50.159
What are you doing here?

23:50.195 --> 23:51.727
I'm catching you on your lie, Captain.

23:51.763 --> 23:55.198
I mean, not only are you
not killing the Dark One,

23:55.233 --> 23:56.666
but you're helping him.

23:56.701 --> 24:01.103
You... You have given up
your great white whale.

24:01.139 --> 24:02.738
[SINGSONGY VOICE] No, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no.

24:02.774 --> 24:05.074
Now there's a fly in the ointment!

24:05.109 --> 24:07.009
[NORMAL VOICE] Don't
listen to his buzzing.

24:07.045 --> 24:08.678
Listen to <i> my</i> voice.

24:08.713 --> 24:10.313
Think of the tower.

24:10.348 --> 24:11.647
Think of your daughter.

24:11.683 --> 24:13.115
Don't listen to that idiot.

24:13.151 --> 24:14.283
Don't let him in your head.

24:14.319 --> 24:16.285
Oh, I'm already in his head.

24:16.321 --> 24:18.233
Look at you.

24:18.654 --> 24:19.856
Look at you,

24:19.891 --> 24:22.091
letting the Dark One do your dirty work

24:22.126 --> 24:23.292
because you can't.

24:23.328 --> 24:25.061
[CHUCKLES] Hell, you can't even save

24:25.083 --> 24:27.166
your own daughter without him.

24:27.232 --> 24:29.265
Tell me... What's her name?

24:29.300 --> 24:30.266
Alice?

24:30.301 --> 24:32.034
Don't you mention her name.

24:32.283 --> 24:34.704
Don't you ever mention her name!

24:34.739 --> 24:36.539
[CHUCKLES]

24:36.574 --> 24:39.636
Tell me, does she know
the truth about her papa?

24:39.661 --> 24:42.512
You want to see the real me?

24:42.547 --> 24:43.913
Then I'm happy to oblige.

24:43.948 --> 24:45.081
[CLICKS TONGUE] Oh, no, no, no, no.

24:45.116 --> 24:47.503
[CHUCKLES] Not here.

24:47.542 --> 24:50.709
I want people to see me defeat you.

24:50.722 --> 24:51.921
By that,

24:52.686 --> 24:56.522
I mean a duel, in public...

24:57.444 --> 24:59.161
in the light of day.

24:59.197 --> 25:01.030
You see, I think it's time

25:01.065 --> 25:03.699
that everyone sees the Hook that I see.

25:03.735 --> 25:05.935
No! Enough! Let me out!

25:05.970 --> 25:08.191
I'll r-r-rip his face
off, take his other leg,

25:08.216 --> 25:10.341
give you his hand... Whatever you want.

25:10.366 --> 25:12.375
No one need know it's me.

25:12.410 --> 25:14.343
And then your legend will live on...

25:14.375 --> 25:16.124
♪ forever. ♪

25:16.125 --> 25:19.208
Otherwise, you are
gonna lose everything.

25:19.284 --> 25:21.117
No.

25:21.152 --> 25:24.453
I think he means that
<i>he's</i> gonna lose everything.

25:24.489 --> 25:25.521
Ignore the imp.

25:25.557 --> 25:28.624
Yeah, but the imp wants what you want.

25:28.660 --> 25:30.726
Freedom calls.

25:30.762 --> 25:34.530
I can help you if you let me.

25:34.566 --> 25:37.066
If you let me out!

25:37.101 --> 25:38.668
No!

25:38.703 --> 25:41.137
No. No, this is my
fight, Rumplestiltskin.

25:41.167 --> 25:43.334
It's a duel you want... Hmm.

25:43.374 --> 25:45.207
Oh, it's a duel you'll get.

25:46.844 --> 25:48.744
Pistols at dawn.

25:48.780 --> 25:50.646
Tomorrow.

25:51.069 --> 25:54.817
ROGERS: My first painting. Happy now?

25:54.852 --> 25:57.053
It's beautiful.

25:57.088 --> 25:59.422
The calm before the storm.

25:59.457 --> 26:01.290
Tell me about the killer.

26:01.326 --> 26:03.826
You don't get answers
until you give some.

26:03.861 --> 26:07.296
Now, come here, look at the painting,

26:07.332 --> 26:10.900
and tell me what it really means to you.

26:11.740 --> 26:13.240
Fine.

26:13.438 --> 26:14.870
[CHAIR SCRAPES]

26:18.459 --> 26:19.459
[SIGHS]

26:19.510 --> 26:21.177
As a child, I loved the ocean.

26:21.209 --> 26:22.626
I always wanted to visit.

26:22.680 --> 26:24.347
Then I grew up, forgot about it,

26:24.382 --> 26:25.448
and it's a distant memory.

26:25.483 --> 26:26.916
That's all.

26:26.951 --> 26:29.885
It must have been quite a day
when you finally got out there.

26:29.918 --> 26:33.294
You must have felt
like a real sea captain.

26:33.626 --> 26:35.542
Actually, I've still never been.

26:35.584 --> 26:37.001
But the ocean's so close.

26:37.028 --> 26:38.961
I mean, why... why not
grab your special someone

26:38.997 --> 26:40.262
and go touch the sea?

26:40.298 --> 26:42.628
Because I don't have anyone!
Is that what you want to hear?!

26:42.653 --> 26:44.100
Yes.

26:45.250 --> 26:48.625
They say all great art starts with pain.

26:49.188 --> 26:51.155
And now I know yours.

26:52.834 --> 26:55.793
The killer is also
grappling with pain...

26:56.570 --> 26:59.147
An unfillable void, if you will.

26:59.187 --> 27:00.248
And just like you, they're looking

27:00.292 --> 27:02.084
for a way to express that pain,

27:02.109 --> 27:06.155
to externalize it in a way
that only makes sense to them.

27:06.190 --> 27:08.524
Both the doctor and the baker were given

27:08.559 --> 27:10.626
a gift before they were attacked...

27:10.662 --> 27:11.827
A heart-shaped candy box

27:11.863 --> 27:13.896
filled with chocolate marzipan truffles.

27:13.931 --> 27:15.264
That's quite specific.

27:15.299 --> 27:17.166
Everyone has their obsessions.

27:17.977 --> 27:19.835
So, if you want to find the killer,

27:19.876 --> 27:23.126
all you have to do is follow your heart.

27:28.125 --> 27:30.709
Ivy. What are you doing here?

27:30.715 --> 27:32.333
I'll tell you what I'm <i> not</i> doing.

27:32.358 --> 27:34.277
Carrying that any further.

27:34.302 --> 27:36.167
Mom saved some of your old stuff.

27:36.192 --> 27:38.099
If you want it, you can take it.

27:39.325 --> 27:41.099
It's nice to see you, too.

27:41.124 --> 27:43.025
Oh, calm down.

27:43.042 --> 27:44.084
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- I just carried a box

27:44.131 --> 27:47.363
full of your stuff to your doorstep.

27:47.783 --> 27:49.188
Didn't even get a thank you.

27:49.213 --> 27:51.133
Why are you really here, Ivy?

27:51.169 --> 27:53.235
To talk about Mom?

27:53.271 --> 27:54.870
Do you even care?

27:54.906 --> 27:56.205
You know, it's been a week now.

27:56.240 --> 27:59.742
Okay, tap your brakes,
Jacinda. I am still processing.

27:59.777 --> 28:01.210
Not everyone has the kind

28:01.245 --> 28:04.380
of mom and daughter relationship
that you have with Lucy.

28:04.415 --> 28:08.617
Yeah, well, everybody
has problems... everybody.

28:09.253 --> 28:10.765
Even me and Lucy.

28:10.790 --> 28:12.121
Wait.

28:12.156 --> 28:14.836
Since when are you two not besties?

28:15.326 --> 28:17.760
Since this morning.

28:17.795 --> 28:19.862
I don't know.

28:19.897 --> 28:22.832
There's something off with her,

28:22.867 --> 28:25.768
and for the first time ever,
I don't have Victoria to blame.

28:25.803 --> 28:28.671
I only have me.

28:28.706 --> 28:32.269
Look, there are so many things
that you do that annoy me,

28:32.294 --> 28:36.479
wallowing in self-pity
being an example.

28:36.514 --> 28:39.014
You're a great mother. That's a fact.

28:39.050 --> 28:40.096
You love your daughter.

28:40.121 --> 28:44.502
And unlike Victoria, you
make sure she knows it.

28:45.372 --> 28:47.237
Well, I try to.

28:47.823 --> 28:49.435
[CLEARS THROAT]

28:49.460 --> 28:51.560
So you did come here to talk.

28:53.131 --> 28:55.397
Next time, just say so.

28:58.250 --> 29:00.209
Mm. Yeah.

29:02.974 --> 29:04.640
You know what?

29:04.675 --> 29:08.511
Actually, I have something for you.

29:10.834 --> 29:14.126
IVY: Hey. [CHUCKLES]

29:14.152 --> 29:16.485
- [CHUCKLES]
- It's Beatrice.

29:16.521 --> 29:18.988
I never thought I'd see her again.

29:19.023 --> 29:22.057
Our childhood seems like so long ago.

29:22.093 --> 29:23.826
Yeah.

29:23.861 --> 29:26.562
Almost like a... Like
another world, right?

29:26.597 --> 29:28.931
Mm. You have no idea.

29:28.966 --> 29:31.467
Hmm.

29:31.502 --> 29:32.735
And you know what?

29:33.198 --> 29:34.804
Now I know what I have to do.

29:35.339 --> 29:37.643
To make it good with Mother.

29:37.668 --> 29:39.956
What do you mean? How?

29:41.078 --> 29:43.010
I have to finish what she started.

29:47.709 --> 29:49.418
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:53.000 --> 29:56.792
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS]

30:02.209 --> 30:08.543
Ten paces. Then turn. Then shoot.

30:08.909 --> 30:10.041
One.

30:13.209 --> 30:15.418
Two.

30:16.185 --> 30:18.419
Three.

30:18.673 --> 30:21.040
Four.

30:21.076 --> 30:23.676
Five.

30:23.712 --> 30:25.450
Six.

30:26.314 --> 30:28.414
Seven.

30:28.989 --> 30:30.221
Eight.

30:31.953 --> 30:34.254
Nine.

30:34.289 --> 30:35.521
Ten!

30:40.562 --> 30:42.595
HOOK: I should call you something.

30:43.834 --> 30:45.043
ALICE: Promise me you'll be okay.

30:45.066 --> 30:46.499
[GUNSHOT]

30:46.534 --> 30:48.868
HOOK: I will return as soon as I can.

30:48.904 --> 30:51.271
- I love you.
- Alice.

30:56.415 --> 30:58.982
[BOTH GROAN]

31:02.167 --> 31:03.584
- [GRUNTS]
- You're fine, sir.

31:03.618 --> 31:05.151
Just nicked...

31:05.186 --> 31:07.987
which is more than I can say for Ahab.

31:08.023 --> 31:09.155
He may survive the day,

31:09.209 --> 31:12.334
but your aim was true as the North Star.

31:12.933 --> 31:14.894
What's the matter, sir?

31:14.930 --> 31:17.330
You did it, Captain! You won.

31:18.824 --> 31:20.967
I haven't won anything that mattered.

31:21.002 --> 31:23.169
[GROANS]

31:23.204 --> 31:27.177
I think... I think I've
made a dreadful mistake.

31:27.412 --> 31:28.841
I have to leave.

31:37.083 --> 31:38.159
ROGERS: The candy store said

31:38.209 --> 31:41.127
this was the last place they
delivered the chocolates to.

31:41.128 --> 31:42.401
You'd think a member of the occult

31:42.417 --> 31:44.792
would work somewhere less cheery.

31:44.824 --> 31:47.315
I think it's about to
get a lot less cheery.

31:49.918 --> 31:51.502
Marzipan truffles.

31:52.018 --> 31:54.644
The woman who runs this
place is the next target.

31:55.747 --> 31:58.081
Hello, there. How can I help you?

31:58.348 --> 31:59.518
Hyperion PD.

31:59.542 --> 32:01.542
We'd like to speak to the
woman who received this package,

32:01.584 --> 32:03.043
A Luanne Hoffs-Drawler.

32:03.088 --> 32:04.354
Is she here?

32:04.389 --> 32:05.589
No.

32:05.883 --> 32:08.692
Luanne was my wife. She
passed away years ago.

32:08.727 --> 32:10.560
What's this all about?

32:12.219 --> 32:14.030
Thank you for your time.

32:16.986 --> 32:18.319
[SIGHS]

32:18.503 --> 32:20.403
This whole thing was a setup.

32:20.439 --> 32:22.372
I warned you of Eloise.

32:22.407 --> 32:24.140
Either she's distracting us,

32:24.167 --> 32:26.626
or the killer is using
her to distract us.

32:26.678 --> 32:27.811
From what?

32:27.846 --> 32:28.907
It's not as if we have any leads

32:28.959 --> 32:30.293
or even know who the next target is.

32:30.315 --> 32:33.617
We know the last one...
The Baker in the hospital.

32:46.042 --> 32:49.751
[ALARM BLARES]

32:57.509 --> 32:59.442
[GASPS]

33:00.478 --> 33:01.844
Tilly.

33:02.776 --> 33:04.222
What are you doing here?

33:04.247 --> 33:06.650
I-I don't know. I,
uh... I had to be here,

33:06.685 --> 33:08.785
but, ugh, I don't want to be.

33:08.820 --> 33:11.788
I-I want to be somewhere
else. Somewhere nice.

33:11.823 --> 33:15.025
Tilly, put the scalpel down.

33:15.042 --> 33:17.459
No. No, really, you're too late.

33:17.496 --> 33:20.163
I tried to warn you,
but you wouldn't listen.

33:20.198 --> 33:21.998
You didn't pay attention to
the thing that matters most,

33:22.034 --> 33:23.888
and that's when people get hurt!

33:23.913 --> 33:25.335
I'm sorry, Tilly.

33:25.370 --> 33:27.366
I should have paid more attention.

33:27.375 --> 33:29.750
Just... Just tell me what
happened. We can help you.

33:29.792 --> 33:31.334
No. You're too late.

33:31.376 --> 33:32.742
Don't you understand?

33:32.879 --> 33:35.673
I told you something
bad would happen today!

33:35.698 --> 33:36.880
And neither of you listened.

33:36.918 --> 33:38.794
- [SCALPEL CLATTERS]
- And now you're both too late.

33:38.834 --> 33:40.376
- Tilly!
- Don't...

33:48.959 --> 33:50.042
Tilly!

34:06.417 --> 34:07.876
Papa!

34:07.913 --> 34:09.951
I was starting to worry.

34:10.792 --> 34:12.167
There's no need to worry, Starfish.

34:12.201 --> 34:13.483
I'm here now.

34:13.507 --> 34:15.842
I have something in here

34:15.879 --> 34:18.980
that can smash this tower to pieces.

34:22.452 --> 34:23.518
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Papa?

34:23.553 --> 34:24.752
Aah!

34:24.788 --> 34:26.054
[WHOOSH]

34:26.089 --> 34:27.422
[WHIMPERS]

34:27.456 --> 34:28.922
Ohh!

34:28.958 --> 34:30.525
What's happening?

34:30.560 --> 34:32.908
[STRAINED] I-I don't know.

34:32.933 --> 34:34.838
But I do.

34:34.862 --> 34:36.408
What did you do to me?

34:36.433 --> 34:38.266
No less than you deserve.

34:38.301 --> 34:39.469
You're poisoned now,

34:39.501 --> 34:42.751
and it will corrupt your heart
every time Alice draws near.

34:42.797 --> 34:43.929
You've both been marked.

34:43.965 --> 34:45.097
Please don't do this.

34:45.132 --> 34:46.966
He's my father. He's a good man.

34:47.001 --> 34:48.900
Not good enough.

34:48.937 --> 34:50.703
Your father went on a little detour

34:50.737 --> 34:53.940
because there's more important
things to him than his daughter.

34:55.179 --> 34:58.493
He fought a duel for his precious honor.

34:58.883 --> 35:00.182
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

35:00.209 --> 35:01.960
You didn't come right back.

35:01.999 --> 35:03.316
You promised me.

35:03.334 --> 35:05.252
I only stopped for a moment. I swear.

35:05.291 --> 35:06.752
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

35:06.788 --> 35:08.415
How did you do this to me?

35:08.459 --> 35:10.918
I simply made sure the
bullet was poisoned.

35:10.943 --> 35:13.243
Your pride did the rest.

35:13.278 --> 35:14.544
[WHOOSH]

35:14.580 --> 35:16.947
Papa!

35:16.982 --> 35:18.460
[SIGHS] Papa.

35:20.959 --> 35:22.918
[GROANS]

35:25.257 --> 35:27.190
[GRUNTS]

35:27.226 --> 35:29.526
You can't keep me from her.

35:29.561 --> 35:31.328
I will get her out.

35:31.363 --> 35:33.130
[GRUNTS]

35:35.067 --> 35:37.701
No.

35:37.736 --> 35:42.205
You will fail her again and again.

35:42.241 --> 35:44.274
You might as well go back to the tavern

35:44.309 --> 35:46.269
and have another drink.

35:46.294 --> 35:49.323
ALICE: Papa, where are you?! Save me!

35:49.348 --> 35:50.447
[GRUNTS]

35:50.482 --> 35:51.948
Such a heartbreaking cry for help.

35:51.984 --> 35:53.750
Papa, please help!

35:53.786 --> 35:56.153
I couldn't let you free her.

35:56.188 --> 35:57.963
And now you never will.

36:01.927 --> 36:05.829
Please, Papa, save me!

36:05.864 --> 36:08.732
Help me, Papa! Please!

36:08.767 --> 36:10.300
Help me!

36:12.345 --> 36:14.296
Tilly?

36:15.374 --> 36:16.540
You here?

36:20.626 --> 36:22.335
[SWITCH CLICKS]

36:35.834 --> 36:39.043
No, no, I know how this looks, but...

36:39.131 --> 36:41.962
there's no way that
Tilly killed those women.

36:41.987 --> 36:43.775
This has to be...

36:43.800 --> 36:46.579
her upside-down thinking gone awry.

36:46.604 --> 36:48.937
I think it's a bit more
than that, actually.

36:50.542 --> 36:53.477
Tilly had, uh, experience

36:53.512 --> 36:55.795
with this cult some years before.

36:55.820 --> 36:57.280
You know, they took the one person

36:57.334 --> 36:59.543
that mattered most to her.

37:00.589 --> 37:04.020
The one person who spent time with her

37:04.056 --> 37:06.105
and who could really understand her.

37:08.619 --> 37:10.452
Her father.

37:11.296 --> 37:14.097
In the eyes of the law, that's motive.

37:14.437 --> 37:18.971
Yeah, but... she's not a killer.

37:22.542 --> 37:25.209
You don't think she did this, do you?

37:27.167 --> 37:29.126
No, of course I don't.

37:31.417 --> 37:34.168
Well, then we're on the same page.

37:34.186 --> 37:36.019
So, how do we make this right?

37:36.054 --> 37:37.787
I'll head back to the station

37:37.823 --> 37:39.156
and buy us the time we need.

37:39.191 --> 37:41.525
But they're gonna want
one of us accountable,

37:41.560 --> 37:43.994
should anything else happen.

37:44.309 --> 37:45.862
So, while I stay there...

37:45.898 --> 37:48.064
I'll find Tilly.

37:48.100 --> 37:49.432
I'll prove her innocence.

37:49.468 --> 37:51.134
Yeah.

38:00.167 --> 38:01.626
Oh.

38:01.667 --> 38:04.593
Mochi from Lucky Cat?

38:05.100 --> 38:07.684
I, uh... I do like mochi.

38:07.719 --> 38:10.754
This is just a thank
you for some good advice.

38:10.789 --> 38:13.326
Well, thank you.

38:13.755 --> 38:15.186
You want to come in?

38:21.889 --> 38:25.235
So, what did I do to deserve
the city's best mochi?

38:25.270 --> 38:27.971
Well, you were right about Jacinda.

38:28.207 --> 38:30.273
There aren't that many
people who really know me,

38:30.309 --> 38:33.339
and I forgot that she does.

38:35.347 --> 38:38.481
Henry, apples don't fall
too far from the family tree.

38:38.517 --> 38:40.417
And, like my mother,

38:40.452 --> 38:44.054
I have done some... horrible things.

38:44.252 --> 38:46.652
And, like her, I need to fix them.

38:48.751 --> 38:52.669
I want you to help me...
to find my other sister,

38:52.698 --> 38:54.368
to find Anastasia.

38:54.650 --> 38:57.625
Wait, wait. Wait. You
have another sister?

38:57.650 --> 38:59.869
Like I said, it's complicated,

38:59.918 --> 39:01.585
and there's a lot you
don't know about me.

39:01.597 --> 39:03.435
But Anastasia has more reason

39:03.459 --> 39:05.377
to hate me than Jacinda ever did.

39:05.834 --> 39:09.379
Okay. And how exactly can I help?

39:09.414 --> 39:12.749
By being who you are deep down.

39:12.784 --> 39:14.184
You might not realize it,

39:14.219 --> 39:18.154
but I think you could
be the hero I need.

39:18.190 --> 39:19.484
Hmm.

39:21.574 --> 39:25.176
Well, then, let's drink to heroes.

39:27.083 --> 39:29.709
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

39:29.735 --> 39:31.701
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ON STEREO]

39:38.083 --> 39:39.417
Oh.

39:39.444 --> 39:40.577
You know we don't serve

39:40.612 --> 39:43.213
shots of strawberry milk here, right?

39:43.497 --> 39:44.614
You better have a good reason

39:44.650 --> 39:46.483
for putting my liquor license at risk.

39:47.271 --> 39:48.918
It's Henry.

39:48.954 --> 39:50.186
I need your help.

39:52.391 --> 39:54.758
This page, it suddenly appeared.

39:54.793 --> 39:58.196
It says Henry is going to
die if he kisses my mom.

39:58.221 --> 39:59.863
So that's why

39:59.898 --> 40:02.365
you stopped them from
kissing last night?

40:02.971 --> 40:04.000
It's all my fault.

40:04.036 --> 40:05.835
I-I found Henry

40:05.871 --> 40:07.804
and... and tricked him into coming here.

40:07.839 --> 40:12.508
And now... now I'm going to lose him.

40:14.437 --> 40:16.413
I know you didn't believe me

40:16.448 --> 40:18.448
when I told you that you
were the Evil Queen, but...

40:18.483 --> 40:21.484
Yeah, well, a lot's
happened since then, Lucy.

40:24.289 --> 40:26.177
And you know what?

40:27.224 --> 40:28.935
I believe you now.

40:29.372 --> 40:31.461
You do?

40:31.496 --> 40:32.629
You've read the book?

40:32.664 --> 40:36.612
Read it? I lived it.

40:37.198 --> 40:38.368
And I am not going to let

40:38.403 --> 40:40.070
my granddaughter face this alone.

40:40.105 --> 40:42.072
So you're awake? I-I knew you were.

40:42.107 --> 40:45.542
You are Regina. So that makes me...

40:45.577 --> 40:48.891
That makes you... a Mills, Lucy.

40:49.164 --> 40:50.513
And so am I.

40:51.258 --> 40:53.550
Just don't call me grandma.

40:53.585 --> 40:57.721
The Mills family does
what heroes do best...

40:57.756 --> 40:59.022
We save people.

40:59.042 --> 41:00.960
- Like my dad?
- Yes.

41:01.459 --> 41:04.668
And we're gonna start exactly
like your father did...

41:04.696 --> 41:09.766
With a set of walkie-talkies
and... an operation name.

41:09.801 --> 41:11.101
Any suggestions?

41:11.136 --> 41:13.002
"Operation Hyacinth."

41:13.334 --> 41:15.626
The first thing my dad gave my mom.

41:15.674 --> 41:18.920
[CHUCKLES] Operation Hyacinth it is.

41:18.983 --> 41:20.477
And what's our next move?

41:20.512 --> 41:22.379
Well, what do you think?

41:22.414 --> 41:24.247
We're gonna give your mother and father

41:24.292 --> 41:26.709
the happy ending they deserve.

